Andhra Pradesh Power Finance Corp., a
state-owned lender to Indiaâ€™s power generators, hired banks to
sell at least 10 billion rupees ($226 million) of 10- and 12-
year bonds, according to a person familiar with the matter.  The 12-year notes will pay a coupon of 8.84 percent and are
redeemable after 10 years, the person said, asking not to be
identified as the details are private. The 10-year notes will
pay 8.49 percent and are redeemable after seven years.  The borrower, based in Hyderabad, hired nine banks to
arrange the issue, which opens on Oct. 11 and closes on Oct. 30
